org.ow2.proactive.scheduler.job

Class JobInfoImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ow2.proactive.scheduler.job.JobInfoImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, JobInfo

    public class JobInfoImpl
extends Object
implements JobInfo
    JobInfo provides some information about the Job it is linked with.
    These information and only them are able to change inside the job, and that's what the scheduler will send to each listener.
    To have a job up to date, you must use org.ow2.proactive.scheduler.job.InternalJob#setJobInfo(JobInfo). This will automatically put the job up to date.
    Since:
    ProActive Scheduling 0.9
    See Also:
